## Enable CAMARA Validation and Release Automation for {{name}}

Following the [Spring26 release announcement](https://lists.camaraproject.org/g/codeowners/topic/119079596) on the codeowners list, this PR onboards **{{name}}** to **CAMARA Validation** and the updated **Release Automation**, plus the CHANGELOG directory structure both depend on.

### What you get

**CAMARA Validation** runs automatically on every PR against `main`, `release-snapshot/**`, or `maintenance/**`:
- Catches compliance and spec issues at PR time, when fixes are cheap
- Inline annotations on the diff plus a structured findings report in the PR check
- Same rule set across all CAMARA APIs, kept current with each Commonalities release

**Release Automation** streamlines the release lifecycle:
- Automates the mechanical steps of cutting a release — version bumps, CHANGELOG entries, release metadata
- Slash commands on Release Issues give explicit control over snapshotting, publishing, and rollback
- Same lifecycle across all CAMARA APIs — predictable, repeatable releases

